### Description

- Adding a TapGestureRecognizer to a span after it's been set to FormattedText on a label doesn't work
- If you now click that Span really fast you'l get an NRE

### Steps to Reproduce

click on the 
*"I will not fire when clicked"*
text and notice nothing happens
click on it really fast and see an NRE exception

```c#
var label = new Label();

			var s = new FormattedString();
			var span = new Span { Text = "I will fire when clicked", FontAttributes = FontAttributes.Bold };
			var span2 = new Span { Text = "I will not fire when clicked", FontAttributes = FontAttributes.Bold };
			span.GestureRecognizers.Add(new TapGestureRecognizer()
			{
				Command = new Command(async () =>
			   {
				   await MainPage.DisplayAlert("Yay clicked", "yay clicked", "yay clicked");
			   })
			});

			s.Spans.Add(span);
			s.Spans.Add(span2);

			label.FormattedText = s;
			span2.GestureRecognizers.Add(new TapGestureRecognizer()
			{
				Command = new Command(async () =>
			   {
					await MainPage.DisplayAlert("not working", "not working", "not working");
			   })
			});

			return new ContentPage()
			{
				Content = new StackLayout()
				{
					Children = { label },
					Padding = 40
				}
			};
```

### Expected Behavior
Both spans should be clickable and clicking rapidly shouldn't cause a NRE

### Actual Behavior
When clicking on the second span nothing happens.
If you click the span really fast it'll cause a NRE

### Basic Information

- Version with issue: 3.1 nightly
- IDE: VS for Mac
- Platform Target Frameworks:  
  - iOS:  11.2

